They're saying if the target is damaged, then the AE doesn't affect players around them.<P>This confuses me because I've seen different results.  In PvE I know you can target an engaged and highly damaged mob and it WILL affect everything around them.  I've visually seen it many times.  Often I intentionally target the damaged one for AE, depending on targeting angles and distance.  Same for RvR.<P>edit..<BR>Although there have been many times I've AE mez'd, not seen any resist messages, yet some things I thought should be mez'd aren't.  There just has to be more to the problem than what's stated above.  Also mez's breaking way to early(on oranges..) with nobody near them, no casters casting other than heals.  Strange things some times.<P>--------------------<P>Ierar<BR>50 Sorcerer Bedevere<BR>40 Body/34 Mind
